CIPHER.277.cipherString: Every science begins as philosophy and ends as art; it arises in hypothesis and flows into achievement.
CIPHER.277.question: A phrase by Will Durant has been encoded using the Aristocrat Cipher. What does it say?
CIPHER.277.author: Will Durant

CIPHER.278.cipherString: Courage is the art of being the only one who knows you're scared to death.
CIPHER.278.question: You came across the following written on a wall in a cave. You notice that it's a quote by Earl Wilson encoded as a Porta cipher using a keyword of BEACH. What does it say?
CIPHER.278.author: Earl Wilson

CIPHER.279.cipherString: La nueva interdependencia electrónica recrea el mundo a imagen y semejanza de una aldea global.
CIPHER.279.question: Someone passed you a piece of paper with this Xenocrypt encoded phrase of a quote by Marshall McLuhan in Spanish using a K1 alphabet with an English keyword. What does it say?
CIPHER.279.author: Marshall McLuhan
CIPHER.279.translation: The new electronic interdependence recreates the world in the image of a global village.

CIPHER.280.cipherString: If all the economists were laid end to end, they'd never reach a conclusion.
CIPHER.280.question: A phrase by George Bernard Shaw has been encoded using the Porta Cipher.  The 40th through 46th cipher characters (AZHNKGR) decode to be NEVERRE. What does it say?
CIPHER.280.author: George Bernard Shaw

CIPHER.281.cipherString: Mucho he escrito; pero lo que yo consideraba defectuoso yo mismo lo encomendaba a las llamas correctoras.
CIPHER.281.question: Ovid has been heard to say the following phrase that has been encoded using the Xenocrypt cipher in Spanish using a K2 alphabet with an English keyword. What does it say?
CIPHER.281.author: Ovid
CIPHER.281.translation: Much have I written; but what I considered faulty I myself committed to the correcting flames.

CIPHER.282.cipherString: If one cannot catch the bird of paradise, better take a wet hen.
CIPHER.282.question: Upon searching a room, the following were found on scraps of paper. You realize it's a quote by Nikita Khrushchev encoded as a Fractionated Morse. You are told that the quote starts with IFONEC. What does it say?
CIPHER.282.author: Nikita Khrushchev

CIPHER.283.cipherString: Radical historians now tell the story of Thanksgiving from the point of view of the turkey.
CIPHER.283.question: Someone passed you a piece of paper with this Aristocrat encoded phrase of a quote. You are told that the word POINT appears in it.  What does it say?

CIPHER.284.question: You found the following carved into the bark of a hollow log. You recognize that it's encoded as a Cryptarithm. What do the values 57178 9123 64120 decode to?

CIPHER.285.cipherString: Oh what a feeling when you happen upon a book that seems to pour truth directly into your head.
CIPHER.285.question: A phrase by Garry Fitchett has been encoded using the Aristocrat Cipher using a K1 alphabet. What does it say?
CIPHER.285.author: Garry Fitchett

CIPHER.286.cipherString: Being brave sometimes means letting someone hold you together when you're falling apart.
CIPHER.286.question: Caitlin Miller offers an observation that has been encoded as a Nihilist Substitution with a keyword of DOUBT and polybius key of HYSTERICAL. What does it say?
CIPHER.286.author: Caitlin Miller

CIPHER.287.cipherString: One of the most striking differences between a cat and a lie is that a cat has only nine lives.
CIPHER.287.question: A quote by Samuel Langhorne Clemens (a.k.a. Mark Twain) has been encoded using the Aristocrat Cipher for you to decode. What does it say?
CIPHER.287.author: Samuel Langhorne Clemens (a.k.a. Mark Twain)

CIPHER.288.cipherString: Everyone has special talents, and it is our duty to find ours and use them well.
CIPHER.288.question: John Templeton offers us some advice that has been encoded as a Nihilist Substitution with a keyword length of 5. The 50th through 59th cipher units (39 34 75 76 66 25 56 77 36 64) decode to be ANDUSETHEM. What does it say?
CIPHER.288.author: John Templeton

CIPHER.289.cipherString: I'm a success today because I had a friend who believed in me and I didn't have the heart to let him down.
CIPHER.289.question: Abraham Lincoln offers an observation that has been encoded as an Aristocrat using a K1 alphabet. What was the K1 Keyword used to encode it?
CIPHER.289.author: Abraham Lincoln

CIPHER.290.question: Someone passed you a piece of paper with this Hill cipher of a Proverb encoded using a keyword of TECH. What does it say?
CIPHER.290.author: Proverb

CIPHER.291.cipherString: I want to compete for championships and for titles and keep going to next level in my career.
CIPHER.291.question: Jermaine Seoposenwe has been heard to say the following phrase that has been encoded using the Aristocrat cipher using a K2 alphabet. What was the K2 Keyword used to encode it?
CIPHER.291.author: Jermaine Seoposenwe

CIPHER.292.cipherString: You must have a clear picture in your mind of what success would look, sound, and feel like.
CIPHER.292.question: David Allen offers an observation that has been encoded as a Complete Columnar. You are told that the quote has SUCCESS somewhere in it. What does it say?
CIPHER.292.author: David Allen

CIPHER.293.cipherString: Success - keeping your mind awake and your desire asleep.
CIPHER.293.question: The following odd symbols were found when a tomb was opened, but you recognized it as a prankster who scratched a quote by Walter Scott on the wall using a Baconian alphabet. What does it say?
CIPHER.293.author: Walter Scott

CIPHER.294.cipherString: Anyone who wanted to sell fish had to get permission from my grandpa. He was known as the cod father.
CIPHER.294.question: Your friend passed you a note in class with this Complete Columnar encoded phrase. You are told that it has TOSELL somewhere in it. What does it say?

CIPHER.295.question: A quote has been encoded using the Cryptarithm Cipher for you to decode. What do the values 7452 6879 1032 decode to?

CIPHER.296.cipherString: To spell out the obvious is often to call it in question.
CIPHER.296.question: You came across the following scrawled on a whiteboard in your classroom. You notice that it's a quote by Eric Hoffer encoded as a Baconian cipher. What does it say?
CIPHER.296.author: Eric Hoffer

CIPHER.297.question: Plato was often heard to say the following phrase which has been encoded as a Hill Cipher using a keyword of REST. What does it say?
CIPHER.297.author: Plato

CIPHER.298.cipherString: Be mindful of your strengths and your opponent's weaknesses to design winning strategies.
CIPHER.298.question: A phrase by Sukant Ratnakar has been encoded using the Aristocrat Cipher using a K1 alphabet. What does it say?
CIPHER.298.author: Sukant Ratnakar

CIPHER.299.cipherString: One of the morals to the story: Don't just study your cards... study the players.
CIPHER.299.question: Niedria Kenny offers an observation that has been encoded as a Complete Columnar. You are told that the quote has EMOR somewhere in it. What does it say?
CIPHER.299.author: Niedria Kenny

CIPHER.300.cipherString: The world of literature is a world where there is no reality except that of the human imagination.
CIPHER.300.question: A quote by Northrop Frye has been encoded using the Aristocrat Cipher for you to decode. You are told that the word HUMAN occurs somewhere in plain text.  What does it say?
CIPHER.300.author: Northrop Frye

CIPHER.301.cipherString: A good book is the purest essence of a human soul.
CIPHER.301.question: Thomas Carlyle offers an observation that has been encoded as a Baconian. You are told that the deciphered text ends with SOUL. What does it say?
CIPHER.301.author: Thomas Carlyle

CIPHER.302.cipherString: Fair and softly goes far in a day.
CIPHER.302.question: A phrase by Proverb has been encoded using the Hill Cipher with a keyword of CYLINDRIC. What does it say?
CIPHER.302.author: Proverb

CIPHER.303.cipherString: Even when the buds cannot bloom, the tree stands firm, patiently awaiting its turn.
CIPHER.303.question: Shree Shambav offers an observation that has been encoded as a Nihilist Substitution with a keyword of EXPAND and polybius key of STRATOSPHERE. What does it say?
CIPHER.303.author: Shree Shambav

CIPHER.304.question: A message encrypted with the Cryptarithm cipher has been received. What do the values 82782 30465 499801 decode to?
